# unitTriangle

- _unitTriangle(x)_

Answer the unit triangle function on the interval _(-1,1)_.

```
>>> 0.8.unitTriangle
0.2
```

Plot:

~~~spl svg=A
(-2 -- 2).functionPlot(unitTriangle:/1)
~~~

![](sw/spl/Help/Image/unitTriangle-A.svg)

Plot in two dimensions:

~~~spl svg=B
(-1 -- 1).surfacePlot { :x :y |
	[x y].unitTriangle * 13
}
~~~

![](sw/spl/Help/Image/unitTriangle-B.svg)

